# Docker build context allowlist (2026-07-09 fleet review V2-DOCK-2).
# docker-compose.v2.yml builds with context: '.' (the repo root), so WITHOUT this file the ENTIRE
# 12sgi-king tree streams to the Docker daemon on every build -- including king_private_src/ (the
# private corporate data room / cap table / investor / charter that .gitignore marks NEVER-public),
# config/ (Stripe + secret configs), .env*, and the private cross-thread bus .dispatch_log.jsonl.
# The shipped image only COPYs services/, so today none of that lands in a layer -- but streaming the
# private/secret tree into the build VM every build is needless exposure, and one careless future
# `COPY . .` would bake secrets into an image. Deny-by-default: exclude everything, re-include only
# what the build needs.
*

# Re-include ONLY the build inputs the services/Dockerfile actually uses.
!services/

# Even inside services/, never ship caches or local state.
services/**/__pycache__/
services/**/*.pyc
services/**/*.db
services/**/.env*
!element_lotus_public/
